<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0619 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reviews main fields of computer application in mining, the advantagesgained and the cost involved. Looks at computer applications in excavationindustry, geology, deposit prospecting and exploitation, mine designand monitoring. Maintains that in the mining industry such high outlaysfor hardware and software as 100,000 US dollars will be quickly paidback. Discusses programs for design of workings and for deposit modeling.Describes the Micro-Minos system which can control haulage, drainingpumps and coal preparation plants. The Proscon system of the Finnishfirm Autocompu for coal preparation plant control with on-line measurementsis also presented. 7 refs.</TEXT></DOC>